gm/rs-plugkit watcher defect witnessed: readWasmStr can heap-corrupt in-memory (wasm-memory-read-out-of-bounds), causing subsequent spool verbs (e.g. git_finalize/git_add) to fail deterministically against a live but corrupted watcher instance. Reproduced with three different payloads, ruling out argument content as the trigger -- points to a use-after-free or stale-offset bug in the wasm memory read path, not a caller-input issue. Recovery: kill the corrupted watcher process and do a genuine fresh boot (bun x gm-plugkit@latest spool); the identical prior call then succeeds immediately with a new pid. This matches the documented dead-watcher recovery protocol but the trigger (heap corruption, not just staleness) is a real rs-plugkit/host-wrapper defect worth root-causing in readWasmStr's bounds handling.